                <head>228. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On October 17, 1962, Brazil and Norway were elected as non-permanent members of
                    the Security Council for 1963, receiving 91 and 85 votes respectively. A second
                    ballot, restricted to Morocco and Nigeria, resulted in Morocco’s election by 73
                    votes to 35. (Memorandum from <persName corresp="#p_WW6">Woodruff
                        Wallner</persName> to Secretary <persName corresp="#p_RD3">Rusk</persName>,
                    October 17; National Archives and Records Administration, RG 59, Central Files
                    1960–63, 330/10–1762)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
